A fire has engulfed a building on Grey Street in Durban. Officials say they can’t confirm yet if the blaze is part of the recent unrest. eNCA senior reporter Dasen Thathiah has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A fire has engulfed a building on Grey Street in Durban. Officials say they cannot confirm yet if the blaze is part of the recent unrest. READ: Two buses torched in Cape Town But the metro cops have confirmed that arson is behind the blaze. The fire has been extinguished.